---
import { env } from 'cloudflare:workers';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Masthead from '../components/Masthead.astro';
import HomeListCard from '../components/HomeListCard.astro';
import Rating from '../components/Rating.astro';
import { getFeaturedRecent } from '../lib/db';

// Pull one well-rated visited place to use as a worked example. Prefer 9+ so
// readers see the high-tier pill treatment in context; fall back to whatever
// is most recent if there isn't one.
const featured = await getFeaturedRecent(env.DB, 5);
const exampleRestaurant = featured.find((r) => r.avg_overall != null && r.avg_overall >= 9) ?? featured[0];
const photosBase = env.PUBLIC_PHOTOS_URL ?? '';
---
<BaseLayout title="About · Lucas Eats Big" description="Hi, I'm Lucas. This is everywhere I've eaten in Sydney.">
  <Masthead active="about" />

  <main class="about">
    <div class="hero">
      <div class="hero-text">
        <h1>Hi <span class="wave" aria-hidden="true">👋</span></h1>
        <p class="hero-sub">This site is the back-end of <a href="https://instagram.com/lucaseatsbig" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">@lucaseatsbig</a>.</p>
        <p>I'm Lucas, I live in Sydney, and I think about food more than is healthy.</p>
        <p>This site is a running record of every restaurant I've been to that I had an opinion about. It started as a Notion database that got too big, then a spreadsheet, and finally something I could send to friends without making them sign up for anything.</p>
        <p>Every entry is mine. Every rating is honest. I pay for everything I eat. No comps, no PR dinners, no agenda. If something's on the wishlist it's because I want to go; if it's rated it's because I went.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="phone" aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="phone-frame">
          <div class="phone-screen">
            <img src="/instagram-profile.png" alt="" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="prose">

      <h2>How I score</h2>
      <p>I rate every visit out of 10, in half-points. There's no formula. It's an overall feel for how good the meal was. Here's how it shows up on the cards:</p>
      <div class="score-tiers">
        <div class="tier-row">
          <div class="tier-pill">
            <Rating value={9.5} size="md" />
            <span class="tier-range">9.0+</span>
          </div>
          <div class="tier-body">
            <h3>Exceptional</h3>
            <p>I'd recommend it to anyone, no caveats. Worth re-ordering your week for.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tier-row">
          <div class="tier-pill">
            <Rating value={8.0} size="md" />
            <span class="tier-range">7.0–8.9</span>
          </div>
          <div class="tier-body">
            <h3>Really good</h3>
            <p>Worth going out of your way for. The bar I want every meal to clear.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tier-row">
          <div class="tier-pill">
            <Rating value={6.0} size="md" />
            <span class="tier-range">Below 7</span>
          </div>
          <div class="tier-body">
            <h3>A mixed bag</h3>
            <p>Fine, disappointing, or "I had to try it once". The number tells the story.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p>If I've been more than once, the number you see is the average across visits. Each visit also has a separate <em>size</em> rating from 1–10, relative to its category. A 9-size burger is huge for a burger, not huge in absolute terms (10 = hard to finish, 1 = barely a snack).</p>
      <p>There's also a <em>would return</em> flag on every visit. Sometimes a place rates a 6 but I'd 100% go back; sometimes an 8 and I'm done with it. The flag captures that separately from the score.</p>

      {exampleRestaurant && (
        <>
          <p class="example-label">For example:</p>
          <div class="example-card">
            <HomeListCard restaurant={exampleRestaurant} photosBase={photosBase} />
          </div>
        </>
      )}

      <h2>What you can filter on</h2>
      <p>Head to <a href="/all">all places</a> and you can slice the list by:</p>
      <ul class="filters">
        <li>
          <strong>Cuisine</strong>
          <p>One primary cuisine per entry. A few of the options:</p>
          <div class="ex-row">
            <span class="ex-cuisine">Japanese</span>
            <span class="ex-cuisine">Italian</span>
            <span class="ex-cuisine">Thai</span>
            <span class="ex-cuisine">Korean</span>
            <span class="ex-more">+ more</span>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Location</strong>
          <p>Pick a Sydney region or a specific suburb. For example:</p>
          <div class="ex-row">
            <span class="ex-location"><span class="pin" aria-hidden="true">●</span>Inner West</span>
            <span class="ex-location"><span class="pin" aria-hidden="true">●</span>Surry Hills</span>
            <span class="ex-location"><span class="pin" aria-hidden="true">●</span>Eastern Suburbs</span>
            <span class="ex-more">+ more</span>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Price</strong>
          <p>Five tiers, multi-select:</p>
          <div class="ex-row">
            <span class="ex-price">$</span>
            <span class="ex-price">$$</span>
            <span class="ex-price">$$$</span>
            <span class="ex-price">$$$$</span>
            <span class="ex-price">$$$$$</span>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Vibe</strong>
          <p>Pick as many as you want. A few of the options:</p>
          <div class="ex-row">
            <span class="ex-vibe">Date spot</span>
            <span class="ex-vibe">Casual</span>
            <span class="ex-vibe">Upscale</span>
            <span class="ex-vibe">Loud</span>
            <span class="ex-vibe">Quiet</span>
            <span class="ex-more">+ more</span>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Top rated</strong>
          <p>One-tap toggle for anything 7 or above:</p>
          <div class="ex-row">
            <span class="ex-toggle"><span class="check">✓</span> Top rated (7+)</span>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Visited vs wishlist</strong>
          <p>See only places I've been, or only ones on the list:</p>
          <div class="ex-row">
            <span class="ex-toggle on">Visited</span>
            <span class="ex-toggle">Wishlist</span>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>Sort by best-first, most-recently-visited, or A–Z.</p>

      <p class="muted">
        Got a place I should try?
        <a href="https://instagram.com/lucaseatsbig" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">tell me</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about {
    max-width: 920px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: clamp(3rem, 8vw, 4rem) clamp(1.25rem, 4vw, 2.5rem) 5rem;
  }
  .hero {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 2rem;
    align-items: stretch;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }
  @media (min-width: 720px) {
    .hero {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;
      gap: 3rem;
    }
  }
  .hero-text {
    min-width: 0;
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 2vw, 1.375rem);
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--ink);
    text-wrap: pretty;
  }
  .hero-text > p { margin: 0 0 1rem; }
  .hero-text > p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  h1 {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: clamp(3rem, 8vw, 4.5rem);
    line-height: 0.95;
    letter-spacing: -0.035em;
    font-weight: 500;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  .hero-sub {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 1.8vw, 1.25rem);
    color: var(--muted);
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.5;
    font-style: italic;
  }
  .hero-sub a {
    color: var(--terracotta);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--terracotta);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .hero-sub a:hover { background: rgba(184, 84, 58, 0.08); }

  /* iPhone mockup — only the top half is visible; the rest fades to background */
  .phone {
    display: flex;
    align-items: stretch;
    justify-content: center;
  }
  .phone-frame {
    position: relative;
    width: clamp(220px, 28vw, 280px);
    height: 100%;
    background: #0c0c0c;
    border-radius: 54px 54px 0 0;
    padding: 5px 5px 0;
    box-sizing: border-box;
    box-shadow:
      0 0 0 1px #3a3a3c inset,
      0 0 0 2.5px #1a1a1a;
    -webkit-mask-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, #000 55%, transparent 100%);
            mask-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, #000 55%, transparent 100%);
  }
  .phone-screen {
    position: relative;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    border-radius: 49px 49px 0 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: #fff;
  }
  .phone-screen img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: top center;
  }
  .wave {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--terracotta);
    display: inline-block;
  }
  .prose {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 2vw, 1.375rem);
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--ink);
    text-wrap: pretty;
  }
  .prose p { margin: 0 0 1rem; }
  .prose h2 {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 1.875rem);
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    margin: 2.5rem 0 1rem;
  }
  .prose ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }
  .prose ul li {
    padding: 0.6rem 0.9rem;
    border-left: 2px solid var(--rule);
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  /* "How I score" tier rows. Each row is self-contained: rating tile + range
     label on the left, heading + body on the right. No cross-row alignment,
     no fixed-width tricks — the grid does the work. */
  .score-tiers {
    margin: 1.5rem 0 2rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .tier-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 120px 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    align-items: start;
    padding: 1.125rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .tier-pill {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }
  .tier-range {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
  }
  .tier-body { padding-top: 0.125rem; }
  .tier-body h3 {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 1.375rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin: 0 0 0.25rem;
  }
  .tier-body p {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--ink);
    opacity: 0.88;
    margin: 0;
  }
  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .tier-row {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 0.625rem;
      padding: 1.125rem 0;
    }
    .tier-pill {
      flex-direction: row;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.75rem;
    }
    .tier-body h3 { font-size: 1.125rem; margin-bottom: 0.125rem; }
    .tier-body p { font-size: 1rem; }
  }

  /* Worked example card — sits below the rating legend. */
  .example-label {
    color: var(--muted);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 0.95em;
    margin: 1.5rem 0 0.6rem;
  }
  .example-card {
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }
  .prose ul.filters {
    gap: 1rem;
  }
  .prose ul.filters li {
    padding: 1rem 1.1rem;
  }
  .prose ul.filters li strong {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.375rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }
  .prose ul.filters li p {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    line-height: 1.45;
  }
  .ex-row {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.4rem;
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
  }
  .ex-row > span {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 0.4rem;
    height: 32px;
    padding: 0 0.95rem;
    min-width: 7rem;
    border-radius: 999px;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    background: var(--bg);
    color: var(--ink);
    line-height: 1;
    box-sizing: border-box;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .ex-more {
    background: transparent !important;
    border: 1px dashed var(--rule-strong) !important;
    color: var(--muted) !important;
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .ex-cuisine {
    background: rgba(184, 84, 58, 0.08) !important;
    border-color: rgba(184, 84, 58, 0.2) !important;
    color: var(--terracotta) !important;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .ex-location {
    background: rgba(45, 69, 56, 0.08) !important;
    border-color: rgba(45, 69, 56, 0.2) !important;
    color: var(--forest-soft) !important;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .ex-location .pin {
    font-size: 0.55rem;
    line-height: 1;
    transform: translateY(-0.5px);
  }
  .ex-price {
    background: var(--ink) !important;
    color: var(--bg) !important;
    border-color: var(--ink) !important;
  }
  .ex-price .sym {
    font-weight: 700;
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
  }
  .ex-vibe {
    background: var(--terracotta) !important;
    color: var(--bg) !important;
    border-color: var(--terracotta) !important;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .ex-toggle {
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-strong) !important;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .ex-toggle.on,
  .ex-toggle:has(.check) {
    background: var(--ink) !important;
    color: var(--bg) !important;
    border-color: var(--ink) !important;
  }
  .ex-toggle .check {
    width: 14px;
    height: 14px;
    border-radius: 3px;
    background: var(--bg);
    color: var(--ink);
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    padding: 0;
    border: none;
  }
  .prose em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--terracotta);
  }
  .prose .muted {
    color: var(--muted);
    font-style: italic;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
  }
  .prose a {
    color: var(--terracotta);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--terracotta);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .prose a:hover { background: rgba(184, 84, 58, 0.08); }
</style>
